<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,485,1134,1159]" pageId="1" pageNumber="174">Description of the male.</emphasis>
Since the species was described for the single female (
<bibRefCitation author="Fisher" box="[1106,1248,1134,1159]" pageId="1" pageNumber="174" refString="Fisher, W. S. (1942) A new species of Buprestidae from Venezuela (Coleoptera). Boletin de Entomologia Venezolana, 1 (4), 89 - 90." type="journal article" year="1942">
Fisher, 
<number box="[1191,1248,1135,1159]" pageId="1" pageNumber="174" value="1942.0">1942</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) and also 
<bibRefCitation author="Cobos" pageId="1" pageNumber="174" refString="Cobos, A. (1972) Ensayo monografico sobre las Anthaxia Eschs. (Coleoptera, Buprestidae) de America. Tercera parte: Subgenero Agrilaxia Kerremans. Archivos de Instituto de Aclimatacion (Almeria), 16, 5 - 235." type="journal article" year="1972">
Cobos (
<number box="[159,217,1171,1195]" pageId="1" pageNumber="174" value="1972.0">1972</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
did not mention a male I am hereby giving a brief diagnosis of the male. It differs from the female by the unicolorous, green elytra without the circumscutellar triangle, entirely green frons with poorly defined, dark, medial stripe, less bright ventral colouration, slightly truncate anal ventrite and by the strongly dentate anal tergite. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[277,358,1278,1303]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 15" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1245,1268]" captionTargetBox="[162,1416,201,1206]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,193,1225]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 15 (not to scale). Figs. 10 – 12: aedeagi. 10 — Agrilaxia (Agrilaxia) balloui Fisher, 1942 (Venezuela, El Valle); 11 — A. (A.) biformis sp. nov., holotype; 12 — A. (A.) venezuelana sp. nov., holotype; Figs. 13 – 15: anal tergites. 13 — A. (A.) biformis sp. nov., male, paratype; 14 — A. (A.) biformis sp. nov., female, paratype; 15 — A. (A.) venezuelana sp. nov., holotype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/239844/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="174">
Fig. 
<number box="[329,358,1279,1303]" pageId="1" pageNumber="174" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
) long, slender, almost spindle-shaped, dorsal surface of parameres uneven.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,774,1447]" pageId="1" pageNumber="174">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,262,1314,1339]" pageId="1" pageNumber="174">Note.</emphasis>
According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Cobos" box="[426,583,1314,1339]" pageId="1" pageNumber="174" refString="Cobos, A. (1972) Ensayo monografico sobre las Anthaxia Eschs. (Coleoptera, Buprestidae) de America. Tercera parte: Subgenero Agrilaxia Kerremans. Archivos de Instituto de Aclimatacion (Almeria), 16, 5 - 235." type="journal article" year="1972">
Cobos (
<number box="[514,574,1315,1339]" pageId="1" pageNumber="174" value="1972.0">1972</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, also one female deposited in 
<collectionCode LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34871" box="[927,1008,1315,1339]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34871" name="Smithsonian Institution, National Museum of Natural History" pageId="1" pageNumber="174">USNM</collectionCode>
was collected on 
<taxonomicName box="[1213,1436,1315,1338]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Datura" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="1" pageNumber="174" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="stramonium">
<emphasis box="[1213,1436,1315,1338]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="174">Datura stramonium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. (
<taxonomicName box="[194,323,1350,1375]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="1" pageNumber="174" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Solanaceae</taxonomicName>
) which is most probably not a host plant. More reliable is the record of 
<emphasis box="[1193,1436,1350,1374]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="174">Meliccocus bijugatus</emphasis>
(
<taxonomicName box="[158,302,1386,1411]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Sapindaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="1" pageNumber="174" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Sapindaceae</taxonomicName>
) as the host plant of this species (
<bibRefCitation author="Fisher" box="[678,822,1386,1411]" pageId="1" pageNumber="174" refString="Fisher, W. S. (1942) A new species of Buprestidae from Venezuela (Coleoptera). Boletin de Entomologia Venezolana, 1 (4), 89 - 90." type="journal article" year="1942">
Fisher, 
<number box="[762,822,1387,1411]" pageId="1" pageNumber="174" value="1942.0">1942</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
